3. cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) - The paper deals with the correctness criterion for the absence of deadlocks, which is a topic related to theoretical computer science.
4. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper deals with the operational properties of the underlying machine, which is a topic related to software engineering.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - Although less likely, the paper deals with the reduction of proof-nets, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms.
